PREP: 10 minutes
COOK: 20 minutes
YIELD: 6 servings

INGREDIENTS:
-- Chickpeas
2 cans chickpeas, drained and rinsed
Olive oil
1/3 cup hot sauce
2 tbs butter
salt and pepper to taste
1 tbs honey
-- Salad
Mixed greens lettuce
Halved cherry tomatoes
Avocado chunks
Diced red onion
Blue cheese
Spicy ranch dressing

DIRECTIONS:
Combine chickpeas and olive oil on baking pan; roast at 450&deg;F for 20 minutes.
In a small saucepan over low heat, add butter, hot sauce, honey, and salt and pepper.
Toss chickpeas and sauce together; there will be sauce left over.
Assemble the salad.

